00:27:38.780 --> 00:27:40.780
Okay,

00:27:40.780 --> 00:27:42.780
can I bookmark the contents of an uploaded file

00:27:42.780 --> 00:27:44.780
if I were to assign the contents

00:27:44.780 --> 00:27:46.780
to a variable?

00:27:46.780 --> 00:27:48.780
Yes, you can do that.

00:27:48.780 --> 00:27:50.780
So, I think this question

00:27:50.780 --> 00:27:52.780
relates to what I said

00:27:52.780 --> 00:27:54.780
about

00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:56.780
a URL

00:27:56.780 --> 00:27:58.780
encoded state

00:27:58.780 --> 00:28:00.780
not being able to contain

00:28:00.780 --> 00:28:02.780
a file.

00:28:02.780 --> 00:28:04.780
So, yes, if you're able to

00:28:04.780 --> 00:28:06.780
take out the contents of that file and save it

00:28:07.380 --> 00:28:09.380
save it to

00:28:09.380 --> 00:28:11.380
a separate value, then you could

00:28:11.380 --> 00:28:13.380
that could be part of the bookmark.

00:28:13.380 --> 00:28:15.380
But you'd have to use that onBookmark

00:28:15.380 --> 00:28:17.380
and onRestore

00:28:17.380 --> 00:28:19.380
because

