00:35:05.780 --> 00:35:07.780
How does the server admin

00:35:07.780 --> 00:35:09.780
manage all saved states?

00:35:09.780 --> 00:35:11.780
Right now

00:35:12.379 --> 00:35:14.379
it's

00:35:14.379 --> 00:35:16.379
each of the saved states

00:35:16.379 --> 00:35:18.379
is just a directory

00:35:18.379 --> 00:35:20.379
with that unique ID.

00:35:20.379 --> 00:35:22.379
For each

00:35:22.379 --> 00:35:24.379
application there's a directory

00:35:24.379 --> 00:35:26.379
that contains

00:35:26.379 --> 00:35:28.379
subdirectories with those names.

00:35:28.379 --> 00:35:30.379
Right now

00:35:30.379 --> 00:35:32.379
we don't have

00:35:32.379 --> 00:35:34.379
for ShinyServer and ShinyServer Pro

00:35:34.379 --> 00:35:36.379
we don't have a really easy administration tool

00:35:36.379 --> 00:35:38.379
for that. Hopefully we will at some point in the future.

00:35:38.379 --> 00:35:40.379
Unfortunately

00:35:40.979 --> 00:35:42.979
what I can say right now is that you could

00:35:42.979 --> 00:35:44.979
sort them by

00:35:44.979 --> 00:35:46.979
their dates

00:35:46.979 --> 00:35:48.979
and do something with it that way.

00:35:48.979 --> 00:35:50.979
Like if you want to just call

00:35:50.979 --> 00:35:52.979
bookmarks

00:35:52.979 --> 00:35:54.979
that were created a long time ago

00:35:54.979 --> 00:35:56.979
or were only accessed within

00:35:58.979 --> 00:36:00.979
or were not accessed recently

00:36:00.979 --> 00:36:02.979
you should be able to do that.

00:36:02.979 --> 00:36:04.979
But there isn't a nice front end tool

00:36:04.979 --> 00:36:06.979
for that. But that's something that hopefully

00:36:06.979 --> 00:36:08.979
we'll be able to bring to

00:36:09.580 --> 00:36:11.580
the various hosting

00:36:11.580 --> 00:36:13.580
platforms.

